China's winter sports athletes are turning to high-tech facilities and advanced approaches in their preparations for the Beijing 2022 Winter Olympics. In the Six-Degree-of-Freedom Oval operated by Beijing Sport University Winter Sports, an anti-dizziness trainer for pilots is introduced to the sports field to help athletes improve their balance. The simulated training system for skiing and skeleton athletes can collect their training data in real time through a high-precision encoder to improve athletes' training and race performance in a targeted manner.